# Tailwind and shadcn/ui Guidelines

## Modern Tailwind Setup

- This project does NOT use a traditional `tailwind.config.js` file
- Tailwind configuration is managed through `components.json`
- CSS variables are defined in `src/app/globals.css`
- Use the `@theme inline` directive in globals.css for theme configuration

## shadcn/ui Component Usage

- Import UI components from `@/components/ui/`
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils.ts` for conditional class merging
- Component variants are defined in their respective files
- Follow the shadcn/ui naming conventions for props and variants

## CSS Variables

- Use CSS variables for colors, spacing, and other design tokens
- Access theme values through the CSS variable system
- Example: `bg-[var(--primary)]` instead of hardcoded colors
- Refer to `globals.css` for the complete list of available variables

## Component Customization

- Extend shadcn/ui components by wrapping them, not modifying source files
- Use composition patterns when building new components
- Maintain consistent styling across custom and shadcn/ui components

## Lucide React Icons

- **Important**: Lucide React icons inherit the parent's color for both background and path by default
- **Specific Issue**: `text-primary` class causes icons to render as solid blocks instead of outlined icons
- When wrapping icons with `text-primary`, you MUST specify a background color
- Use `bg-transparent` if no background color is needed
- Use a different background color (e.g., `bg-primary/10`, `bg-white`) if you want a visible background
- **Example**: `<div className="text-primary bg-transparent"><Icon /></div>` or `<div className="text-primary bg-primary/10"><Icon /></div>`
- **Note**: Other text color classes like `text-white`, `text-[#hexcode]` work fine without background specification
